=======================
NOTE FOR share/ folder:
=======================

This directory contains the configuration files of videomass:
the 'vdms' folder contains Videomass presets files with the 
extension '* .vdms'.
the *.vdms files, are simple xml files need for presets list;
the videomass.conf and the videomassWin32.conf are the main 
configuration files to store the user preferences.

When running the program as the first run, the contents of this folder 
is copied to the default location of the 'videomass' configuration 
directory, according to the conventions typical of each Operating 
System.
        On *nix OS's:   '~/.config/videomass'
        On MacOs:       '~/Library/Application Support/videomass'
        On Windows:     'C:\Users\username\AppData\Roaming\videomass'

Also, is used to store the log files of the conversion processes
and to store the new personal profiles.

